GRAPH <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_Narrative_AttendanceGrantsAccess> {
  <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_Narrative_AttendanceGrantsAccess> a narr:Digest ;
    narr:digestOf <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_AttendanceGrantsAccess> ;
    narr:childCount "32"^^xsd:integer ;
    narr:generatedFrom "53f9889402ea2f13767fd3e09126d25cd1181a86" ;
    narr:narration """The July 14 session established a [unified access model](narr:Expr_1MvpV2ConcisionOneProductRulings_110) for the MVP, centering on attendance as the primary membership primitive. The team moved away from fragmented, multi-tier access paths in favor of a [simplified collaborator-plus-explicit-share structure](narr:Expr_1MvpV2ConcisionOneProductRulings_48). Under this ruling, [attendance grants page access](narr:Expr_1MvpV2ConcisionOneProductRulings_107), and cross-memory navigation is resolved by checking access to the target call. While [digest narrations are provisionally visible](narr:Expr_1MvpV2ConcisionOneProductRulings_109) as abstractions of the source, the team acknowledged this remains a [point of tension](narr:Expr_1MvpV2ConcisionOneProductRulings_111) regarding data leakage. The discussion also touched on [future-state subagent perspectives](narr:Expr_1MvpV2ConcisionOneProductRulings_50) and the necessity of [CTA placeholders for orphaned nodes](narr:Expr_1MvpV2ConcisionOneProductRulings_37), while deferring more granular [stripped or tiered sharing](narr:Expr_1MvpV2ConcisionOneProductRulings_121) to V2 work.""" ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Expr_1MvpV2ConcisionOneProductRulings_100> ;
